The paper also discusses the Tanner graph, which is a common tool used in network information theory, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing code ensembles, which is a topic related to statistical inference and machine learning, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the performance of codes with increasing block length, which is a topic related to algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category.
